    <h2>Finland has one of the world's highest rates of seasonal depression</h2>
    <p class="subtitle">From November to February, large parts of Finland experience near-total darkness. The human biological clock depends on light — and kaamos disrupts it profoundly.</p>
    <div class="stat-boxes">
